snippet.title: Jetha क्यों बुला रहा है Bhide को आधी रात में?|Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah|Jo Jetha Wahi Sikander
snippet.description:
Click here to Subscribe to LIV Comedy: 
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCBIT1FSJW6yTlzqK-31FDWg?sub_confirmation=1

A scared Popatlal calls Bhide at midnight and requests him to provide him Mukti Maa’s cell phone number. Popatlal creates panic in Gada's house as he reveals to Daya that Mukti Maa has told him that his bad period will begin soon. But Jethalal does not believe in him and all of them visit Mehta’s house to find a solution. He advises Jethalal to meet Dr. Hathi, but he strictly disagrees with giving any medicine to Popatlal.

Show Name - Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah
Star Cast - Dilip Joshi, Disha Vakani, Amit Bhatt
Episode - 934
Produced By - Asit Kumar Modi, Neela Asit Modi

#taarakmehtakaooltahchashmah #livcomedy #tmkoc #comedy2024 #तारकमेहताकाउल्टाचश्मा #comedy #jethalal #tarakmehta 
 
About The Show:
----------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a comedy show inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada Family which consists of uneducated businessmen Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal’s Wife Daya & their naughty Son Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society' and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. In case of a problem and emergency, Jethalal Gada often rushes to Taarak Mehta to seek his help and guidance as he finds a philosopher in him. The housing society residents help each other find solutions when facing common, real-life challenges and getting involved in sticky situations.

Click here to watch all the episodes of 'Jo Jetha Wahi Sikander' : https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLSXTaG1fT0cTWbYoG3SaD_hKNC0g53ugi

Shiddat Digitally Presented by Cerelac

Asra, a beautiful and cherished young woman, has led a life filled with love and care from her family. In contrast, Sultan, a determined and charismatic perfectionist, overcomes the challenges of his troubled childhood to consistently achieve his desires.

Despite their stark personality differences, Asra falls in love with Sultan. However, after they marry, Asra realizes that Sultan is not the ideal man she had envisioned. To please him, she sacrifices her desires and undergoes a significant transformation.

This revelation becomes the catalyst for an unending series of problems between them. The journey through marital life becomes a complex maze as Asra and Sultan attempt to navigate challenges, each trying to mold the other according to their own will and preference.

Will Asra and Sultan change for each other, or will the growing list of problems between them persist? When Asra discovers the reality about Sultan, how will she react? Is Sultan contemplating leaving Asra? Can love overcome all obstacles, or are some differences too profound to bridge?

snippet.title: Jiya Laage Na (Official Video) Shilpa Rao, Mohit Chauhan, Rochak Kohli | Isha Malviya,Parth Samthaan
snippet.description:
Presenting the official video of "Jiya Laage Na" composed by Rochak Kohli, and sung by the maestros Mohit Chauhan and Shilpa Rao, will envelope you with its warmth of love. Rochak has created a melody that inherently and effortlessly draws you in to its world. The words are simple, yet not simplistic, the symphony is gentle yet impactful, and the hook line provides the perfect bind in bringing all the emotions together.

The music video is shot with soft focus, featuring the most popular Parth Samthaan and Isha Malviya. It’s a simple story of a newly married couple finding love and each other in a joint family set-up. Its looking for tender moments of togetherness snatched away from everyone that captures the essence of the song.

Jiya Laage Na is that restless ode of love, of longing and finally, finding a common love language.

snippet.title: മധുരക്കിനാവ് പോലൊരു ലീലാമ്മ  | VIRAL DANCE LEELAMMA JOHN | ORU MADHURA KINAVIN
snippet.description:
അടുക്കളയിൽ കരിക്കറിഞ്ഞ് മുരടിക്കാനുള്ളതല്ല പെണ്ണുങ്ങളുടെ ജീവിതം ;'ഒരു മധുരക്കിനാവിൻ' പാട്ടിന് ചുവടു വെച്ച വൈറൽ ലീലാമ്മയുടെ മാസ് ഡയലോഗ്

സിനി ആര്‍ട്ടിസ്റ്റ് അവയ് സന്തോഷിന്റെ അമ്മയാണ് ലീലാമ്മ ജോൺ. പട്ടാമ്പിയില്‍ ഒരു ബന്ധുവിന്റെ വിവാഹച്ചടങ്ങിനിടയിലാണ് ലീലാമ്മ കുട്ടികൾക്കൊപ്പം വെറുതെ ഡാൻസ് ചെയ്തത്. മകൻ സന്തോഷ് ഈ ഡാൻസിന്റെ വീഡിയോയെടുത്ത് വെറുതെ സോഷ്യൽ മീഡിയയിൽ പോസ്റ്റ് ചെയ്തു. മണിക്കൂറുകൾക്കുള്ളിൽ മില്യൺകണക്കിനാണ് വ്യൂസ് വന്നത്.

ഒരു മധുരക്കിനാവിൻ | Evergreen Film Song | Oru Madhurakinavin | Kanamarayathu | Malayalam Film Song 
#orumadhurakinavin #kanamarayath #orumadurakinavin #yesudas #evergreensong 
#kairalitv  #viraldance 

song credit 
Music: ശ്യാം
Lyricist: ബിച്ചു തിരുമല
Singer: കെ ജെ യേശുദാസ്
Film/album: കാണാമറയത്ത്

ഒരു മധുരക്കിനാവിൻ ലഹരിയിലെങ്ങോ
കുടമുല്ലപ്പൂവിരിഞ്ഞൂ
അതിലായിരമാശകളാലൊരു പൊൻ‌വലനെയ്യും
തേൻ‌വണ്ടു ഞാൻ
അലരേ തേൻ‌വണ്ടു ഞാൻ
(ഒരു മധുരക്കിനാവിൻ )

അധരമമൃതജലശേഖരം, നയനം മദനശിശിരാമൃതം
ചിരിമണിയിൽ ചെറുകിളികൾ
മേഘനീലമൊഴുകി വരൂ പൂഞ്ചുരുള്‍ ചായല്‍
എന്തൊരുന്മാദം എന്തൊരാവേശം
ഒന്നു പുൽകാൻ ഒന്നാകുവാൻ

snippet.description:

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

---------
Dilip Joshi as Jethalal Champaklal Gada
Disha Vakani as Daya Jethalal Gada
Nitish Bhaluni / Raj Anadkat / Bhavya Gandhi as Tipendra Jethalal Gada (Tapu)

आप सबको शक्ति और शालीनता के एकल पर्याय, विद्या के सर्वश्रेष्ठ प्रतीक, बजरंग बली महावीर हनुमान जन्मोत्सव की ढेर सारी शुभकामनाएँ! 🙏🏻💐इस पुण्य-अवसर पर अपने-अपने राम ऊर्जा-सत्र का यह विशेष प्रसंग आप सबकी आस्था को सादर समर्पित है। 😍🙏🏻

-------------------------------------------------------------------
About Dr Kumar Vishwas :

The people who make history are the ones who not only give their life to their career but also give their career a new life. When the career is that of a poet, every step is a risk. Kumar Vishwas is one such poet who has gifted himself an era of such a popularity which other poets cant’t even dream of.
Kumar Vishwas is a poet who went beyond the stereotypical norms of ‘Kavi Sammelan’ or poetic functions and made it a performer’s stage. He has mastered and excelled in all aspects in whatever he has done. Dr Kumar Vishwas has been doing this since years just with a mic and his poems and wits in his soulful voice.
His popularity can be guessed by the fact that the audience sings his verses with him, he has crafted a new dimension by rejuvenating the structure and mechanics of Hindi poetry and Kavi Sammelan.
 
Recently, Dr. Kumar Vishwas has started hosting energy sessions popularly Known as Apne Apne Ram and Apne Apne Shyam where he talks about life skills of Shri Ram’s and Shri Krishna's life, and the applicability of the same in one’s own life to over come the challenges and social concerns we come across in our life.

snippet.description:
Click here to subscribe to SAB: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC6-F5tO8uklgE9Zy8IvbdFw?sub_confirmation=1

Episode 4049: Sharbat Ya Sharab?
--------------------------------------------------------
The Purush Mandal reveals their plan for an April Fool's prank on the Mahila Mandal and Popatlal, but Popatlal remains skeptical. Later, the Mahila Mandal decides to taste the drink in the bottle to verify if it's alcohol or juice. Will they discover the truth?

Show Name – Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah
Star Cast –  Dilip Joshi, Disha Vakani, Amit Bhatt, Nitish Bhaluni
Episode No - 4049
Produced By - Asit Kumarr Modi

#TaarakMehtaKaOoltahChashmah #तारकमेहताकाउल्टाचश्मा #sab #Latest #New #TaarakMehtaKaOoltahChashmah2023 #tmkocfunnyepisodes #hindicomedy #comedyvideo 

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in 'Gokuldham Co-operative Society' and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. The show predominantly - promotes 'Jethalaal' (Dilip Joshi), a Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Shailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Nitish Bhaluni). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises.

Click here to watch all the episodes of Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:  https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL6Rtnh6YJK7ZFhouqhrvP3Sx0U7qxdzJi

snippet.title: A Day at TV Serial Set 📺 | Take A Break
snippet.description:
Get ready for a hilarious peek behind the scenes in our newest comedy sketch, "A Day at the TV Serial Set"! 🎬🤣
Join us as we take you on a wild ride through the chaotic world of Indian television serials, where melodrama reigns supreme and the antics behind the camera are just as entertaining as the stories unfolding on screen.
In this laugh-out-loud sketch, we introduce you to a motley crew of characters that populate the set of a typical TV serial. From the overzealous director with a penchant for dramatic gestures to the perpetually stressed-out production assistant juggling a million tasks at once, each member of the crew adds their own unique flavor to the comedy mix.


Produced By - Monica Prabhudesai
Line Producer - Pratik Thakur
Creative Producer- Ravindra Sarowar

Script - Mohd. Zaid
Direction - Sayali Sonule
1st AD- Satyam Phule
2nd AD- Shreyas Koli

snippet.description:

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

---------
Dilip Joshi as Jethalal Champaklal Gada

*About* 
------------
